(2) The Judical Service Commission may at any time appoint any person to undertake the duties of an Under- Sheriff under the provisions of this Act during the absence of such Under- Sheriff from the place in which he has his office, and whilst undertaking such duties such person shall be deemed to be an Under- Sheriff for the purposes of this Act. [As amended by G.N. No. 303 of 1964, and Act No. 3 of 1989 ]
